      },
      "date": "2020-02-24 22:36:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It wouldn't be terrible to add osc_spin_is_locked() to spelling.txt.\n\nDo you mean \"spin_is_locked()\" ??\nIt is valid to use it outside of asserted ... though there seem to be fewer than 5 valid uses in all of linux.\nI doubt it is really worth adding to spelling.txt.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "453d6b66e327b112273999882152f9e008216d09",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-02-25 04:01:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> > It wouldn't be terrible to add osc_spin_is_locked() to\n > spelling.txt.\n > \n > Do you mean \"spin_is_locked()\" ??\n > It is valid to use it outside of asserted ... though there seem to\n > be fewer than 5 valid uses in all of linux.\n > I doubt it is really worth adding to spelling.txt.\n\nSorry, I meant osc_object_is_locked().  The function was removed.  That said, I don't think this is a widely-used function, so the chance of having in-flight patches using it is low, and they would fail the build anyway.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
